    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The mother should enter upon her work with courage and energy, relying constantly upon divine aid in all her <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"266\"></span> efforts. She should never rest satisfied until she sees in her children a gradual elevation of character, until they have a higher object in life than merely to seek their own pleasure.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 5-25-1882\" data-link=\"820.4387\">The Signs of the Times, May 25, 1882</span>.</span></a></sup>",
