    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Cultivate the Good; Repress the Evil</strong>&mdash;Parents are to co-operate with God by bringing their children up in His love and fear. They cannot displease Him more than by neglecting to train their children aright.... They are to carefully guard the words and actions of their little ones, lest the enemy shall gain an influence over them. This he is intensely desirous of doing, that he may counterwork the purpose of God. Kindly, interestedly, tenderly, parents are to work for their children, cultivating every good thing and repressing every evil thing which develops in the characters of their little ones.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">16<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Ms 49, 1901\" data-link=\"14066.8925001\">Manuscript 49, 1901</span>.</span></a></sup>",
